Moyes was unimpressed by Mitrovic's reaction -- the Serbia striker went down clutching his face -- but said the referees needed to be stronger in their decision-making.
"Every footballer has a responsibility to do the correct thing but the officials are giving the players responsibility to gain success by their actions," he said on Monday.
